<li>a general feeling of tiredness</li>
<li>muscle pains and cramps</li>
<li>muscle twitches</li>
<li>slurred speech</li>
<li>weakness in the arms and legs.</li>
</div>
<button class="accordion">What is the main cause of motor neuron disease?
</button>
<div class="panel">
<p>Motor neurone disease occurs when specialist nerve cells (motor neurones) in the brain and spinal cord progressively lose their function. It's not clear why this happens. In most cases, a person with motor neurone disease won't have a family history of the condition.<a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/products/motor-neurone-disease-awareness-e-learning-course-cpd-certified?variant=6902262530082"_blank""><font color="green"><u>Click here for Online Motor Neurone Disease Training Courses.</u></font></a></p><p></p>
